groups and evaluation of information received in response to a 

Federal Register

 notice. A technology review is a shorter evaluation of a technology; it may be performed if the medical or scientific
questions posed are limited, the available evidence is limited and the published medical literature is insufficient
in quantity or quality, or the time frame available precludes utilization of the full assessment process. 
